place_collected: North America: Canada, Nunavut, Victoria I. (NU), Read Island
description: Seems that this is smaller and darker-flowered than Mackenzie distr. plant. Diam. of expanded fl. 1.5 cm. Petals 1.2 cm. long, lamina orbicular, deep purple, 0.7 cm. long and broad, claw very narrow, pale. Sepals reddish-green, 0.8 cm., strongly keeled +/- saccate. Stamens about 0.8 cm., filaments thick, tapering, anthers small elongate about 2 mm. long. Stigma coronate, sessile. Infl. at anthesis short and dense, shorter than thinly appressed purplish leaves, soon elongating. Siliques 4-5 cm. long, +/- curved, valves keeled, purplish green.
site_desc: Read Island off south coast of Wollaston Peninsula.
